<span id="freeTextContainer10038691296211264585">Made me realize how shallow my knowledge of the civil rights movement and MLK&apos;s role was ... and most likely still is. Though it skims quickly over his youth and the indiscretions of his adult years, it&apos;s hard to imagine a more complete biography. In reading bios of Washington, MLK, and other icons I&apos;ve realized that what I&apos;m looking for are the dimensions that turn them from symbols into men, flawed and human in their greatness.</span>
