<div id="review_1044034171" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1044034171" />
    <a title="Karen Masso" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22915892-karen-masso"><img alt="Karen Masso" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1375919931p2/22915892.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1044034171?book_show_action=true">Sep 02, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Karen Masso" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Karen Masso" href="/user/show/22915892-karen-masso">Karen Masso</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1044034171" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4588668082591378001">This is a super-detailed book on the facinating life of a man who shaped a nation.<br/><br/>I was surprised and encouraged by messiness of the story. The nation&apos;s injustices abounded. The civil rights movement was chock full of organizations who couldn&apos;t agree on things like strategy or use of money. There were ambitious people, turf issues and times when pride got in the way. MLK, Jr himself was a gifted, yet flawed man. <br/><br/>That is where the hope lies, in the humanity of the players. The movement leaders wh</span>
  <span id="freeText4588668082591378001" style="display:none">This is a super-detailed book on the facinating life of a man who shaped a nation.<br /><br />I was surprised and encouraged by messiness of the story. The nation's injustices abounded. The civil rights movement was chock full of organizations who couldn't agree on things like strategy or use of money. There were ambitious people, turf issues and times when pride got in the way. MLK, Jr himself was a gifted, yet flawed man. <br /><br />That is where the hope lies, in the humanity of the players. The movement leaders where ordinary people. MLK, Jr was an ordinary man, but had an extra-ordinary God. That was encouraging to me. God makes his power perfect in weakness. <br /><br />At the same time, MLK, Jr. was uniquely gifted for this role. He taught and lived forgiveness and love for enemies. His eloquence, intelligence and ability to inspire was incredible.<br /><br />I am so grateful for his life and ministry.<br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="4588668082591378001" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


